1
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:29,680
The clothes she's wearing in the photo,

2
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:32,810
how come they're the same as what Li Na wore when she died?

3
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:41,200
Oh, her. Her name is Jiajia.

4
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:42,450
She quit yesterday.

5
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:43,980
Give me her ID info.

6
00:00:44,480 --> 00:00:45,440
No, you just...

7
00:00:45,440 --> 00:00:47,200
I advise you to think carefully before answering me.

8
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:48,240
Don't hide what you know.

9
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:49,500
She's a major suspect.

10
00:00:51,680 --> 00:00:52,520
Whether she's a suspect or not,

11
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:53,200
the thing is,

12
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,200
in our industry,

13
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:56,000
turnover is pretty high.

14
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:59,120
We really don't ask about these things.

15
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:00,180
Ask about what?

16
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:02,170
Why are you here?

17
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:04,200
I saw that Polaroid on your desk,

18
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:05,660
so I guessed you'd be here.

19
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:07,640
Not bad, kid.

20
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:09,250
Worked overtime all night?

21
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,580
What's the deal with the girl?

22
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:12,650
He said she quit.

23
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:15,440
When?

24
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:16,920
Officers.

25
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:21,480
I thought about it all night.

26
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:24,280
I feel I still need to tell you.

27
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:27,680
Actually,

28
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:29,800
I've actually been to Na's house.

29
00:01:30,039 --> 00:01:31,640
But it has nothing to do with me.

30
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:33,759
Na asked Linda to deliver medicine.

31
00:01:33,759 --> 00:01:35,560
And Linda asked me to go instead.

32
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:39,850
Liu Qing.

33
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:41,440
What's wrong, Linda?

34
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,380
Could you do me a favor?

35
00:01:48,759 --> 00:01:50,920
Na, it's Liu Qing.

36
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:57,080
Na, Linda asked me to bring you the medicine.

37
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,260
Na, here's your medicine.

38
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:01,320
Oh, Liu Qing.

39
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:04,680
Na was still alive when I left.

40
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:06,920
I'm so stupid.

41
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:09,490
Why didn't I notice something was wrong then?

42
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:14,000
Sister Na must have scolded me to make me leave just to protect me.

43
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:33,160
Are you sure you'll leave here once you get the money?

44
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:34,079
Trust me.

45
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:38,200
Promise me you won't hurt anyone, okay?

46
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:09,320
Leave the rest to me.

47
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:35,640
Brother, I know I was wrong.

48
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:38,120
I shouldn't have yelled at you just now.

49
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,840
Why, Jiajia?

50
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,800
Why did he treat me like this?

51
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:45,250
Because you have money.

52
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:49,720
I have money? Linda has even more money than me.

53
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,600
They usually bully you too.

54
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:54,760
Why don't you target her?

55
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:55,960
Jiajia.

56
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:58,520
Jiajia, please talk to Hua.

57
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:00,240
On your first day of work,

58
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,000
didn't I help you out?

59
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,120
Say something.

60
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,640
Please plead for me.

61
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:07,240
Jiajia, please say something for me.

62
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,530
Jiajia, please say something for me, Jiajia.

63
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:17,240
According to Liu Qing, an employee of Qianye,

64
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:20,320
Li Na had given this blue dress to Jiajia,

65
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:22,640
but it appeared at the crime scene again.

66
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:23,520
What does this mean?

67
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:25,760
It's highly possible that Jiajia was at the scene.

68
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:29,000
Jiajia quit her job right after the incident.

69
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,000
So we can basically confirm

70
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,880
that this girl named Jiajia is a prime suspect.

71
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,640
Who is this woman named Jiajia?

72
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:36,720
We have questioned all the relevant staff at the nightclub,

73
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:38,920
but we still don't have her detailed information.

74
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:41,640
Looking for a former entertainment venue employee,

75
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:43,080
isn't that like looking for a needle in a haystack?

76
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,320
Of course there's more.

77
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:45,680
Based on the case analysis,

78
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:47,520
this Jiajia is likely a bait.

79
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,360
The actual perpetrator is someone else.

80
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:51,040
Moreover, both victims were wealthy.

81
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:54,320
It's safe to say this was a premeditated murder for money.

82
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,440
Ma.

83
00:04:59,159 --> 00:05:02,040
To be able to kill two adult women without leaving a trace,

84
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:03,040
I guess

85
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:05,440
it must be someone familiar with the surroundings

86
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:08,160
and a habitual offender with some criminal experience.

87
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,200
As for Guangnan,

88
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:09,920
you see, for so many years,

89
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:12,120
there hasn't been a criminal of such a vicious case.

90
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:13,640
Having one appear out of thin air

91
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:14,920
is not impossible,

92
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:17,320
but the probability is extremely low.

93
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,400
So I suggest

94
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:21,240
we should start by investigating the released prisoners

95
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:22,240
here in Guangnan.

96
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,530
Do you solve cases purely by guessing?

97
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,120
If we investigate like you said...

98
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,400
Are we looking for a needle in a haystack?

99
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,730
Isn't yours a guess too?

100
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,400
I inferred it based on evidence.

101
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:33,640
Yours is a pure guess.

102
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:36,560
Just tell me if my previous judgment was right or not.

103
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,120
Right.

104
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,320
You were right this time.

105
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:39,080
What about next time?

106
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,440
Are you going to guess every time?

107
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:43,120
The probability of rolling a dice would be higher.

108
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:46,250
Neither of your investigation directions is a problem.

109
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:49,520
Ma, investigate the released prisoners.

110
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:52,000
Lin Wei followed Jiajia's lead.

111
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:55,130
Hasn't it been confirmed to be a murder for money?

112
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:58,000
Find someone to check their bank statements.

113
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,040
Captain Li, let me check the bank statements.

114
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,000
Okay. Go now.

115
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:01,520
Okay.

116
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:09,280
Sister Na, stop talking nonsense.

117
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,260
How much money do you have?

118
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,800
I have a few thousand in cash.

119
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,930
I also have a gold watch.

120
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,480
Nothing else.

121
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,480
Where is it?

122
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:29,200
In the tin box in the first drawer.

123
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:54,320
A Hong Kong boss gave me that watch.

124
00:06:58,159 --> 00:06:59,080
Is that all?

125
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:02,800
Sister Na.

126
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:06,760
This perfume of yours alone is not cheap.

127
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,880
And you told me you don't have money?

128
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:19,600
It's mine now.

129
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:24,000
Anything else?

130
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:27,560
Bro, I really have nothing left.

131
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,720
You're not lying?

132
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:34,320
I'm not lying to you.

133
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:37,680
I don't think you're taking this very seriously.

134
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:42,080
Bro, I really have no more money.

135
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,960
I just look glamorous on the outside.

136
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:51,360
Actually, I sent most of my money back to my hometown.

137
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,600
The transfer records are in the drawer.

138
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,860
Brother Hua, I'm begging you.

139
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:59,000
Please let me go. I'm begging you.

140
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:04,160
You just said that Linda

141
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,600
bullied my woman?

142
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,240
Is she richer than you?

143
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:10,720
Her?

144
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,720
She started earlier than me.

145
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,680
Sister Na, it's Liu Qing.

146
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,280
Sister Na.

147
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:25,040
Sister Na, I'm here to bring you your medicine.

148
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,240
Don't think just because I was nice to you,

149
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,400
you can push your luck

150
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,600
and think we can be friends.

151
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,640
I'm telling you,

152
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:31,000
you are not worthy of taking Linda's place.

153
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:31,800
Get out!

154
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,039
It's not this person.

155
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,080
She has no money.

156
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,480
She's broke.

157
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:42,280
Ask Jiajia if you don't believe me.

158
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:43,799
I didn't know she would come.

159
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:45,200
I called Linda.

160
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:48,520
You just said Linda isn't coming.

161
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:51,280
You'll get another scar right here.

162
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:54,410
Let's see how you make money to raise your daughter then.

163
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:57,400
Do you hear me?

164
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:06,320
Linda, it's Nana.

165
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,740
Why aren't you coming?

166
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,400
Nana.

167
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:11,210
I was just about to tell you.

168
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:13,760
It's not that I don't want to run errands for you.

169
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:15,360
I have to work and make money.

170
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:18,040
Linda, I'm not asking you to run errands for me.

171
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:20,520
I mainly want to talk to you about the subletting business.

172
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:22,320
Haven't you always wanted to do this?

173
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:24,760
Let's figure out how much it is.

174
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:25,960
Bring your bankbook.

175
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,720
We'll finalize it today.

176
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:38,680
Nana.

177
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,360
Why are you here?

178
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:47,610
Are you here to do business with Na?

179
00:09:48,920 --> 00:09:51,200
I also want to join Na and Linda

180
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:53,200
to learn how to make some extra money.

181
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,800
Na is waiting for you inside.

182
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:58,200
How much money do you have

183
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,530
for Na to take you along?

184
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:02,480
Na.

185
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:03,400
Linda.

186
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:07,880
Jiajia.

187
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:10,080
Who is this country bumpkin?

188
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,560
You really like bullying others, don't you?
